- Creating files
- Importing files
- Deleting and editing files
- Image view (PNG / other common formats)
- Map view (map8, map16)
- Text view
- Model view
- Group names
- Audio
- 'Go To Instance' menu
- References
- Class names for PROP objects
- Property editing
- Having multiple packages merged into one session
- Hotkeys
- Add an actual search function
- Add more reverse hashes + reverse hashes for groups
- Script editor
- Building viewer
- SCRUI editor (separate program?)

Activation
----------
- Figure out where the decryption key and IV are
- Figure out where to use the key and IV / start of encrypted binary

Engine
------
- Due for rewrite, rlWebKit is in dire need of cleaning up having been filled with too much SimCity cruft for what started as a dependency completely unassociated with SimCity.
- Updater -> Launcher3D -> Game: How does this flow work?
- Find where in the game it says to go to Updater.html. Will need advanced editor for that.
- Updater: Actually update?

File Formats
------------
- RW4: Full support, also rename to Rdx9, its proper name. Perhaps a rewrite is in order
- BNK crashes often. Why?
- ww2ogg: Can't seek generated OGGs. This is low priority.
- MFS: Gather More info. This is SDelta/GDelta/SLDelta format.
- Statefile: Gather more info. This is singleplayer save file format. It's probably the same files used by the server.
- CRCBin: Work out how to use this format to checksum downloaded update files
- Rules: Gather more info. Low priority.
- Rast: Sync with RW4 format?
- Heightmap: This is the key to creating custom regions as it contains that kind of information. However, there are multiple types of files under this heightmap umbrella. I believe it should be renamed to map or resmap.

Updater
-------
- Make it an API so the engine can call it if we want that
- Checksum the files using CRC
- Extract the 7z files to a prefix for installation
- Download EcoGame scripts?
